If you want the workflow to run on any branch push, you can simply remove the branches filter:

name: Hello World workflow

on:
  push:

jobs:
  hello_world_job:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    steps:
      - name: Print Hello World
        run: echo "Hello, World!"

      - name: Print current date and time
        run: date

This will trigger on pushes to all branches.

Alternative: Explicitly match all branches

You can also write:

on:
  push:
    branches:
      - '**'

or

on:
  push:
    branches:
      - '*'

However, the simplest and most common approach is just:

on:
  push:
If you want all branches except some

For example, run on every branch except production:

on:
  push:
    branches-ignore:
      - production

Or exclude multiple branches:

on:
  push:
    branches-ignore:
      - production
      - master

So for "run on any branch", use:

on:
  push: